в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ  в”Ӯ\n84: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Return  в”Ӯв—Җв”Җв”Җв”Ӯ  Scheduleв”Ӯв—Җв”Җв”Җв”Ӯ  Delete  в”Ӯв—Җв”Җв”Җв”Ӯ  Expired в”Ӯв—Җв”Җв”Җв”ӮCalculate в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n85: в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  Result  в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ  Requeue в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ  Resourceв”Ӯ   в”Ӯ  ?       в”Ӯ   в”ӮIdle Time в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ\n86: в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ   в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ  в”Ӯ\n87: в”Ӯ                                                                              в”Ӯ\n88: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### Component Interactions\n92: \n93: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n94: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n95: | **Reconciler** | Core reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime | context.Context, reconcile.Request | reconcile.Result, error |\n96: | **AgentRuntimeInterface** | Typed client for AgentRuntime CRUD | AgentRuntime objects | AgentRuntime operations |\n97: | **IdleTimeoutChecker** | Determines if resource has exceeded idle timeout | AgentRuntime status | bool (expired), time.Duration (remaining) |\n98: | **CleanupExecutor** | Performs the deletion of expired resources | AgentRuntime reference | error |\n99: | **RequeueCalculator** | Calculates next requeue time | remaining duration | reconcile.Result |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Directory Structure\n104: \n105: ```\n106: pkg/agentd/\n107: в”ңв”Җв”Җ controller.go         # Main reconciler implementation (~180 lines)\n108: в”ңв”Җв”Җ controller_test.go    # Unit tests for reconciler (~200 lines)\n109: в”ңв”Җв”Җ config.go             # Controller configuration (~80 lines)\n110: в”ңв”Җв”Җ metrics.go            # Prometheus metrics for cleanup operations (~60 lines)\n111: в””в”Җв”Җ doc.go                # Package documentation (~20 lines)\n112: \n113: cmd/agentd/\n114: в””в”Җв”Җ main.go               # Controller entry point (~100 lines)\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ## Data Structures\n120: \n121: ### Domain Types\n122: \n123: #### Reconciler\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: // Reconciler reconciles AgentRuntime objects for idle cleanup.\n127: type Reconciler struct {\n128:     // Client is the Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime resources\n129:     client client.Client\n130:     \n131:     // Scheme is the runtime scheme for type registration\n132:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n133:     \n134:     // Clock provides time functionality (allows mocking in tests)\n135:     Clock Clock\n136:     \n137:     // Metrics collects operational metrics\n138:     Metrics *Metrics\n139: }\n140: \n141: // Clock abstracts time operations for testability.\n142: type Clock interface {\n143:     Now() time.Time\n144: }\n145: \n146: // realClock implements Clock using the system clock.\n147: type realClock struct{}\n148: \n149: func (c *realClock) Now() time.Time {\n150:     return time.Now()\n151: }\n152: \n153: // NewReconciler creates a new AgentRuntime idle cleanup reconciler.\n154: func NewReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme) *Reconciler {\n155:     return &Reconciler{\n156:         Client:  client,\n157:         Scheme:  scheme,\n158:         Clock:   &realClock{},\n159:         Metrics: newMetrics(),\n160:     }\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### IdleTimeoutConfig\n165: \n166: ```go\n167: // IdleTimeoutConfig holds the idle timeout configuration.\n168: type IdleTimeoutConfig struct {\n169:     // DefaultTimeout is the fallback timeout when not specified in spec\n170:     DefaultTimeout time.Duration\n171:     \n172:     // MaxTimeout is the maximum allowed idle timeout\n173:     MaxTimeout time.Duration\n174:     \n175:     // MinTimeout is the minimum allowed idle timeout\n176:     MinTimeout time.Duration\n177: }\n178: \n179: // DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig returns the default configuration.\n180: func DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig() IdleTimeoutConfig {\n181:     return IdleTimeoutConfig{\n182:         DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n183:         MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n184:         MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n185:     }\n186: }\n187: \n188: // Validate checks if the configuration is valid.\n189: func (c *IdleTimeoutConfig) Validate() error {\n190:     if c.DefaultTimeout < c.MinTimeout {\n191:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is less than minimum %v\", \n192:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MinTimeout)\n193:     }\n194:     if c.DefaultTimeout > c.MaxTimeout {\n195:         return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is greater than maximum %v\",\n196:             c.DefaultTimeout, c.MaxTimeout)\n197:     }\n198:     return nil\n199: }\n200: ```\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 1236. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018  \n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n- **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n- **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775882335335,"end":1775882335373}}}}
