{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775882424704,"sessionID":"ses_2852a811cffeR7DoAWEXcjqL5o","part":{"id":"prt_d7ad74cc3001dvsHvBGKCeaboI","messageID":"msg_d7ad726c9001jAP9OWjiooZN6c","sessionID":"ses_2852a811cffeR7DoAWEXcjqL5o","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:20","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":200,"offset":350},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n350: | `FlagError` | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n351: | `ConfigError` | Kubernetes config loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n352: | `ConnectionError` | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n353: | `SchemeError` | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n354: | `ServerError` | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n355: | `WorkspaceError` | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n356: \n357: ### Exit Codes\n358: \n359: | Exit Code | Meaning |\n360: |-----------|---------|\n361: | 0 | Clean shutdown |\n362: | 1 | Configuration error |\n363: | 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n364: | 3 | Server startup error |\n365: | 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n366: | 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n367: \n368: ---\n369: \n370: ## Security Considerations\n371: \n372: ### RBAC Requirements\n373: \n374: #### agentd\n375: | Resource | Verbs |\n376: |----------|-------|\n377: | `sandboxes` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` |\n378: \n379: #### router\n380: | Resource | Verbs |\n381: |----------|-------|\n382: | `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n383: \n384: #### workload-manager\n385: | Resource | Verbs |\n386: |----------|-------|\n387: | `agentruntimes` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n388: | `codeinterpreters` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n389: | `pods` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n390: | `secrets` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n391: \n392: #### picod\n393: - Runs inside sandbox pod with container-local permissions\n394: - Workspace directory isolation\n395: - No Kubernetes API access required\n396: \n397: ### Sensitive Data\n398: - Redis passwords via environment variables (not flags)\n399: - Kubernetes service account tokens (in-cluster) or kubeconfig files\n400: - No secrets logged at startup\n401: \n402: ---\n403: \n404: ## Impact Analysis\n405: \n406: ### Files Created\n407: \n408: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n409: |------|--------------|-------------|\n410: | `cmd/agentd/main.go` | ~80 | Idle cleanup controller entry point |\n411: | `cmd/router/main.go` | ~100 | Session routing proxy entry point |\n412: | `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | ~120 | Sandbox orchestration entry point |\n413: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | ~90 | Sandbox daemon entry point |\n414: \n415: ### Dependencies\n416: \n417: ```go\n418: import (\n419:     \"flag\"\n420:     \"os\"\n421:     \"os/signal\"\n422:     \"syscall\"\n423:     \"time\"\n424:     \"context\"\n425:     \n426:     // Kubernetes\n427:     \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n428:     \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n429:     \n430:     // HTTP\n431:     \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n432:     \n433:     // Storage\n434:     \"github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\"\n435:     \"github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\"\n436:     \n437:     // AgentCube internal\n438:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd\"\n439:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router\"\n440:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n441:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod\"\n442:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n443: )\n444: ```\n445: \n446: | Package | Purpose |\n447: |---------|---------|\n448: | `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Kubernetes controller framework |\n449: | `k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd` | K8s config loading |\n450: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP framework for router |\n451: | `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | Redis client |\n452: | `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | Valkey client |\n453: \n454: ### Downstream Consumers\n455: \n456: | Consumer | Usage |\n457: |----------|-------|\n458: | Helm Charts | Deploy binaries as container images |\n459: | Dockerfiles | Build container images for each binary |\n460: | CI/CD | Build and test binaries |\n461: | Local Development | Run services locally with `go run` |\n462: \n463: ### Performance Characteristics\n464: \n465: | Binary | Memory (est.) | Startup Time | Notes |\n466: |--------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n467: | agentd | ~50MB | <5s | Reconciler only, no HTTP server |\n468: | router | ~30MB | <3s | Depends on Redis connection |\n469: | workload-manager | ~60MB | <5s | Controller + HTTP server |\n470: | picod | ~20MB | <2s | Lightweight daemon |\n471: \n472: ---\n473: \n474: ## Alternatives Considered\n475: \n476: ### Alternative 1: Single Binary with Subcommands\n477: \n478: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n479: |--------|------------|\n480: | **Pros** | Simpler deployment; single artifact; shared code |\n481: | **Cons** | Larger binary size; violates microservices pattern; harder to scale independently; all components must be updated together |\n482: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” AgentCube follows microservices architecture; independent scaling and deployment are requirements |\n483: \n484: ### Alternative 2: Configuration Files Instead of Flags\n485: \n486: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n487: |--------|------------|\n488: | **Pros** | More configuration options; easier to manage complex configs; version controlled |\n489: | **Cons** | Additional file management; less explicit; harder to debug; requires config reloading logic |\n490: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Flags are simpler for containerized environments (12-factor app); config files can be added later if needed |\n491: \n492: ### Alternative 3: Environment Variables Only\n493: \n494: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n495: |--------|------------|\n496: | **Pros** | Cloud-native; works well with Kubernetes secrets; no command-line exposure |\n497: | **Cons** | Less discoverable; no built-in help; harder to validate at startup |\n498: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” Flags provide better UX and discoverability; env vars can supplement flags for secrets |\n499: \n500: ### Alternative 4: Sidecar Pattern for picod\n501: \n502: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n503: |--------|------------|\n504: | **Pros** | Separation of concerns; independent updates |\n505: | **Cons** | More complex deployment; networking overhead; requires shared filesystem |\n506: | **Decision** | **Rejected** вҖ” picod is designed to run inside sandbox pods as the main process; sidecar adds unnecessary complexity |\n507: \n508: ---\n509: \n510: ## Risks and Mitigations\n511: \n512: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n513: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n514: | Flag parsing inconsistencies across binaries | Medium | Low | Use shared flag helper functions; consistent naming conventions |\n515: | Missing required flags in production | Medium | High | Fail fast with clear error messages; validate all required flags before startup |\n516: | Graceful shutdown timeout too short | Low | Medium | Configurable timeout with sensible default (30s); log warnings on timeout |\n517: | Kubernetes config loading failures | Medium | High | Support both in-cluster and external configs; clear error messages |\n518: | Redis connection failures at startup | Medium | High | Retry with exponential backoff; fail fast after retries |\n519: | Binary size bloat from dependencies | Low | Medium | Use build flags `-ldflags=\"-s -w\"`; multi-stage Docker builds |\n520: | Signal handling race conditions | Low | Medium | Use context-based shutdown; proper goroutine synchronization |\n521: | Port conflicts | Low | Medium | Configurable ports; check port availability; clear error messages |\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ## Verification\n526: \n527: ### Build Verification\n528: \n529: ```bash\n530: # Build all binaries\n531: go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\n532: go build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\n533: go build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n534: go build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n535: \n536: # Verify binaries exist\n537: ls -la bin/\n538: ```\n539: \n540: ### Help Verification\n541: \n542: ```bash\n543: # Each binary should print help\n544: ./bin/agentd --help\n545: ./bin/router --help\n546: ./bin/workload-manager --help\n547: ./bin/picod --help\n548: ```\n549: \n\n(Showing lines 350-549 of 615. Use offset=550 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| `FlagError` | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n| `ConfigError` | Kubernetes config loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n| `ConnectionError` | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n| `SchemeError` | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n| `ServerError` | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n| `WorkspaceError` | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n\n### Exit Codes\n\n| Exit Code | Meaning |\n|-----------|---------|\n| 0 | Clean shutdown |\n| 1 | Configuration error |\n| 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n| 3 | Server startup error |\n| 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n| 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n\n---\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775882424694,"end":1775882424701}}}}
