”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ       в–ј         в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ    в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ HTTP    в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в”Ӯ Server  в”Ӯ    в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ    в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ       в”Ӯ         в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в”Ӯ  pkg/picod      в”Ӯ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ                                                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ          в”Ӯ                                                                   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ          в–ј                                                                   в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ    Sandbox Pod (isolated)                                                    в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ design.md                   # This file\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ agentd/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                 # Idle cleanup controller entry point (~80 lines)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ router/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                 # Session routing proxy entry point (~100 lines)\nв”ңв”Җв”Җ workload-manager/\nв”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                 # Sandbox orchestration entry point (~120 lines)\nв””в”Җв”Җ picod/\n    в””в”Җв”Җ main.go                 # Sandbox daemon entry point (~90 lines)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Common Flag Types\n\n```go\n// GracefulShutdownConfig holds graceful shutdown configuration.\ntype GracefulShutdownConfig struct {\n    // Timeout is the maximum time to wait for graceful shutdown\n    Timeout time.Duration\n    // Signals lists the OS signals to handle for graceful shutdown\n    Signals []os.Signal\n}\n\n// DefaultGracefulShutdownConfig returns the default configuration.\nfunc DefaultGracefulShutdownConfig() GracefulShutdownConfig {\n    return GracefulShutdownConfig{\n        Timeout: 30 * time.Second,\n        Signals: []os.Signal{syscall.SIGINT, syscall.SIGTERM},\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### agentd Configuration\n\n```go\n// AgentdConfig holds the agentd binary configuration.\ntype AgentdConfig struct {\n    // Kubeconfig is the path to kubeconfig file (empty = in-cluster)\n    Kubeconfig string\n    // SyncPeriod is the full sync period for all AgentRuntimes\n    SyncPeriod time.Duration\n    // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n    GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\n// DefaultAgentdConfig returns the default configuration.\nfunc DefaultAgentdConfig() AgentdConfig {\n    return AgentdConfig{\n        Kubeconfig:      \"\",\n        SyncPeriod:      5 * time.Minute,\n        GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### router Configuration\n\n```go\n// RouterConfig holds the router binary configuration.\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    // Port is the HTTP server port\n    Port int\n    // Debug enables debug logging\n    Debug bool\n    // RedisAddr is the Redis/Valkey server address\n    RedisAddr string\n    // WorkloadManagerURL is the workload manager service URL\n    WorkloadManagerURL string\n    // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n    GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\n// DefaultRouterConfig returns the default configuration.\nfunc DefaultRouterConfig() RouterConfig {\n    return RouterConfig{\n        Port:            8080,\n        Debug:           false,\n        GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### workload-manager Configuration\n\n```go\n// WorkloadManagerConfig holds the workload-manager binary configuration.\ntype WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n    // Port is the HTTP API server port\n    Port int\n    // Kubeconfig is the path to kubeconfig file (empty = in-cluster)\n    Kubeconfig string\n    // RedisAddr is the Redis/Valkey server address\n    RedisAddr string\n    // DefaultImage is the default sandbox image\n    DefaultImage string\n    // Namespace is the default namespace for resources\n    Namespace string\n    // GracefulTimeout is the graceful shutdown timeout\n    GracefulTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\n// DefaultWorkloadManagerConfig returns the default configuration.\nfunc DefaultWorkloadManagerConfig() WorkloadManagerConfig {\n    return WorkloadManagerConfig{\n        Port:            8080,\n        DefaultImage:    \"ubuntu:22.04\",\n        Namespace:       \"default\",\n        GracefulTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### picod Configuration\n\n```go\n// PicodConfig holds the picod binary configuration.\ntype PicodConfig struct {\n    // Port is the HTTP server port\n    Port int\n    // Workspace is the workspace root directory\n    Workspace string\n    // ReadHeaderTimeout is the HTTP read header timeout\n    ReadHeaderTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\n// DefaultPicodConfig returns the default configuration.\nfunc DefaultPicodConfig() PicodConfig {\n    return PicodConfig{\n        Port:              8080,\n        Workspace:         \".\",\n        ReadHeaderTimeout: 10 * time.Second,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Binary Entry Points\n\nEach binary follows the same basic structure:\n\n```go\nfunc main() {\n    // 1. Parse flags\n    config := parseFlags()\n    \n    // 2. Validate configuration\n    if err := validateConfig(config); err != nil {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n        os.Exit(1)\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Log startup\n    logStartup(binaryName, version, config)\n    \n    // 4. Initialize dependencies\n    ctx := setupSignalHandler()\n    \n    // 5. Start service (blocking)\n    if err := run(ctx, config); err != nil {\n        fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %v\\n\", err)\n        os.Exit(3)\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Service Startup Interface\n\n```go\n// Runnable represents a service that can be started and stopped.\ntype Runnable interface {\n    // Start begins the service and blocks until context cancellation or error.\n    Start(ctx context.Context) error\n    // Stop initiates graceful shutdown with the given timeout.\n    Stop(timeout time.Duration) error\n}\n```\n\n### Flag Parsing Contract\n\nAll binaries use the standard Go `flag` package:\n\n| Binary | Flag | Type | Default | Required | Description |\n|--------|------|------|---------|----------|-------------|\n| agentd | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | No | Path to kubeconfig |\n| agentd | `--sync-period` | duration | 5m | No | Full sync period |\n| agentd | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n| router | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP server port |\n| router | `--debug` | bool | false | No | Debug logging |\n| router | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Redis address |\n| router | `--workload-manager` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Workload manager URL |\n| router | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n| workload-manager | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP API port |\n| workload-manager | `--kubeconfig` | string | \"\" | No | Path to kubeconfig |\n| workload-manager | `--redis-addr` | string | \"\" | **Yes** | Redis address |\n| workload-manager | `--default-image` | string | ubuntu:22.04 | No | Default image |\n| workload-manager | `--namespace` | string | default | No | Default namespace |\n| workload-manager | `--graceful-timeout` | duration | 30s | No | Shutdown timeout |\n| picod | `--port` | int | 8080 | No | HTTP server port |\n| picod | `--workspace` | string | . | No | Workspace directory |\n| picod | `--read-header-timeout` | duration | 10s | No | Read header timeout |\n\n### Kubernetes Client Integration\n\nBinaries that interact with Kubernetes use the client-go library defined in `deployment/client-go.md`:\n\n```go\n// createK8sClient creates a Kubernetes client from configuration.\nfunc createK8sClient(kubeconfig string) (*kubernetes.Clientset, error) {\n    // Build config from kubeconfig or in-cluster\n    config, err := clientcmd.NewNonInteractiveDeferredLoadingClientConfig(\n        &clientcmd.ClientConfigLoadingRules{ExplicitPath: kubeconfig},\n        &clientcmd.ConfigOverrides{},\n    ).ClientConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load kubeconfig: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Create clientset\n    clientset, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create clientset: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    return clientset, nil\n}\n```\n\n### controller-runtime Integration\n\n```go\n// createManager creates a controller-runtime manager.\nfunc createManager(kubeconfig string, syncPeriod time.Duration) (ctrl.Manager, error) {\n    config, err := ctrl.GetConfig()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to get config: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(config, ctrl.Options{\n        Scheme:     scheme,\n        SyncPeriod: &syncPeriod,\n    })\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create manager: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    return mgr, nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Code | Description | Binary |\n|-------|------|-------------|--------|\n| `FlagError` | 1 | Missing or invalid CLI flags | All |\n| `ConfigError` | 1 | Configuration loading failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n| `ConnectionError` | 2 | Redis/Valkey connection failure | router, workload-manager |\n| `SchemeError` | 2 | CRD scheme registration failure | agentd, workload-manager |\n| `ServerError` | 3 | HTTP server startup failure | router, workload-manager, picod |\n| `WorkspaceError` | 2 | Workspace initialization failure | picod |\n\n### Exit Codes\n\n| Exit Code | Meaning |\n|-----------|---------|\n| 0 | Clean shutdown |\n| 1 | Configuration error |\n| 2 | Dependency initialization error |\n| 3 | Server startup error |\n| 130 | Interrupted (SIGINT) |\n| 143 | Terminated (SIGTERM) |\n\n### Error Propagation\n\n```go\n// FatalError represents an error that should cause immediate exit.\ntype FatalError struct {\n    Code    int\n    Message string\n    Cause   error\n}\n\nfunc (e *FatalError) Error() string {\n    if e.Cause != nil {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", e.Message, e.Cause)\n    }\n    return e.Message\n}\n\n// Wrap wraps an error with a fatal error code.\nfunc Wrap(code int, message string, err error) *FatalError {\n    return &FatalError{Code: code, Message: message, Cause: err}\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Testing\n\n```go\n// Test flag parsing\nfunc TestParseFlags(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name     string\n        args     []string\n        expected Config\n        wantErr  bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name: \"default values\",\n            args: []string{\"cmd\"},\n            expected: Config{\n                Port: 8080,\n                // ...\n            },\n        },\n        // ...\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Testing\n\n| Test | Command | Expected |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| Build | `go build ./cmd/agentd/...` | Binary compiles |\n| Help | `./bin/agentd --help` | Usage printed, exit 0 |\n| Missing flags | `./bin/router` | Error printed, exit 1 |\n| Graceful shutdown | `timeout 2 ./bin/picod` | Exit 0 |\n\n### Build Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build all binaries\ngo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\ngo build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router\ngo build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager\ngo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\n\n# Verify binaries exist\nls -la bin/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.19.0 | Kubernetes controller framework |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes client library |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.32.0 | Kubernetes API machinery |\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | latest | HTTP framework for router |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.7.3 | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.56 | Valkey client |\n\n### Internal Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd` | Idle cleanup reconciler |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/router` | Session routing handlers |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` | Sandbox orchestration |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Sandbox daemon |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` | CRD types |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store` | Redis/Valkey store |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go` | Generated Kubernetes client |\n\n---\n\n## Integration with client-go\n\nThe binaries that interact with Kubernetes use the generated client-go library from `deployment/client-go.md`:\n\n### Clientset Usage\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned\"\n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n\n// Create clientset\nconfig, _ := ctrl.GetConfig()\nclientset, _ := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n\n// Access typed clients\nagentRuntimes := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace)\ncodeInterpreters := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace)\n```\n\n### Informer Usage\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go/informers/externalversions\"\n)\n\n// Create informer factory\nfactory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 5*time.Minute)\n\n// Get informers\nagentRuntimeInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()\ncodeInterpreterInformer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().CodeInterpreters()\n```\n\n---\n\n## Performance Characteristics\n\n| Binary | Memory (est.) | Startup Time | Notes |\n|--------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n| agentd | ~50MB | <5s | Reconciler only, no HTTP server |\n| router | ~30MB | <3s | Depends on Redis connection |\n| workload-manager | ~60MB | <5s | Controller + HTTP server |\n| picod | ~20MB | <2s | Lightweight daemon |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### RBAC Requirements\n\n#### agentd\n| Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n|----------|-----------|-------|\n| `agentruntimes` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` |\n| `agentruntimes/status` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `update`, `patch` |\n\n#### router\n| Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n|----------|-----------|-------|\n| `secrets` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n\n#### workload-manager\n| Resource | API Group | Verbs |\n|----------|-----------|-------|\n| `agentruntimes` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n| `codeinterpreters` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n| `codeinterpreters/status` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `get`, `update`, `patch` |\n| `pods` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch` |\n| `secrets` | \"\" | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `create`, `update`, `patch`, `delete` |\n\n#### picod\n- Runs inside sandbox pod with container-local permissions\n- Workspace directory isolation\n- No Kubernetes API access required\n\n### Sensitive Data Handling\n- Redis passwords via environment variables (not flags)\n- Kubernetes service account tokens (in-cluster) or kubeconfig files\n- No secrets logged at startup\n\n---\n\n## Build and Deployment\n\n### Makefile Targets\n\n| Target | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `build-agentd` | Build agentd binary |\n| `build-router` | Build router binary |\n| `build` | Build workload-manager binary (default) |\n| `build-all` | Build all binaries |\n| `run` | Run workload-manager locally |\n| `run-router` | Run router locally |\n| `docker-build` | Build workload-manager Docker image |\n| `docker-build-router` | Build router Docker image |\n| `docker-build-picod` | Build picod Docker image |\n\n### Docker Images\n\n| Binary | Dockerfile | Image Name |\n|--------|------------|------------|\n| workload-manager | `docker/Dockerfile` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n| router | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n| picod | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | `picod:latest` |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [client-go Library](../deployment/client-go.md) вҖ” Generated Kubernetes client\n- [Deployment Design](../deployment/design.md) вҖ” Helm charts and Dockerfiles\n- [project.md](../project.md) вҖ” Project context and architecture\n- [pkg/agentd](../pkg/agentd/) вҖ” Idle cleanup controller package\n- [pkg/router](../pkg/router/) вҖ” Session routing package\n- [pkg/workloadmanager](../pkg/workloadmanager/) вҖ” Sandbox orchestration package\n- [pkg/picod](../pkg/picod/) вҖ” Sandbox daemon package\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/cmd/design.md","time":{"start":1775882666134,"end":1775882666145}}}}
